5:
On behalf of the alliance, I, Lilith
Stratos do hereby declare!
6:
From this day forth, humans, fiends,
and elves shall swear to never
invade each other's lands again,
and strive to maintain an
everlasting peace!
13:
I went over the contents of that
speech countless times, and yet I
still find it difficult to deliver it with
such... formality.
17:
A little bravado goes a long way,
wouldn't you say?
26:
So, the races have signed a peace
treaty, right? But they're still not
going to interfere with each other's
affairs?
31:
Precisely. Far too much blood has
been spilled to speak of joining
hands and working together.
Especially between men and fiends.
35:
The fiends will need a new realm to
call their own. Once we've found it,
we'll apply the same technique the
elves did and erect a barrier around
it.
37:
We are not strong enough as a
people to pursue such lofty ideals as
forgiveness.
41:
I see... Well, that might be for the
best.
43:
But I think I know a few people who
would be more than willing to try to
work on improving relations!
45:
We'll have to take it slow at first, of
course... But they might be able to
help!
49: I don't plan on staying here for long.
52:
My people are without a home, and
it falls on me to find it for them. But it
must be somewhere far from here.
54:
If, during my journey, those
acquaintances of yours were to
seek me out, I would not be averse
to lending them an ear.
62:
What of you? It seems you have
completed your initial goal. What
lies in store for you?
66:
Good point... I guess I'll try to find a
way back home? And explore the
Kaleidoscope in the meantime, of
course.
68:
We finally got all the coordinates,
but I still haven't gotten my
memories back. I have no idea
where I even came from.
73:
Th-that sounds serious! Yet you
speak so casually of it.
77:
Alk. That sword you bear—where did
you obtain it?
81:
Oh, this thing? I've had it on me ever
since I arrived in Starview Village...
84:
Now that I think about it, it's
probably not mine. Who knows,
though?
87: If it's not yours, then whose is it?
90:
No idea. To be honest, I also don't
have any clue why I was even able
to use a sword to begin with.
92:
I suppose that's my next mission—to
find out who I really am.
97:
I see. Before you lies a grand
adventure... In that case, I cannot
ask this task of you. Perhaps the
Champion would be better suited
for it?
101: You have a favor to ask of Light?
105:
Hey, there you are.
This a war buddy of yours?
109:
No. This is my parents'. It seems their
grave was moved here from my
hometown.
112:
I... wasn't able to properly say
goodbye to them. My father died
while I was off adventuring... And my
mother passed at some point in the
fifty years I was gone.
114:
Looking back on it, I should have
shown them more respect.
118:
Parents, huh? Can't say I'm an expert
on the topic. What was it like to have
parents?
122:
I... loved them. Dearly. And they
returned that love in kind.
125:
I now fully understand the words
that Rustamov spoke to me. Love
was what kept me going despite it
all...
128:
Was that not the case for you too,
Nimbus?
131:
Heh. Don't you think it's a bit early to
be saying stuff like that? We've only
known each other for a year.
144:
Light, would you like to become an
advisor?
148:
Lilith asked specifically for you to
help out with the restoration of her
world. She's prepared a special
position for you and everything.
152:
An advisory position? That sounds
an awful lot like politics to me... You
know I'm not well-suited for that
manner of work.
157:
Come on, you could totally be their
official mascot or somethin'.
162:
I'm sure even just your presence
would be a great help for Lilith. She
needs someone to rely on.
171:
Fine. But I have one final person that
I wish to help before that. Once I've
done so, I will accept Lilith's proposal.
175: Huh? Who are you talking about?
182:
I told you that I would help you find
your home, didn't I? Our journey is
far from over.
Isn't that right, Stella?
191:
But, where do we even go from
here? We have no clues to go off.
What's left? To just plunge into the
unknown without a plan?
195:
Sounds exactly like what we always
do.
204:
Well then, Alk.
Will you take me along on your new
journey?
